at the expected boost in stellar accretion (or tidal\ndisruption, which could be observed as X-ray flares) in the presence of a gas\ndisc is about a factor of 10. Even with this boost, the accretion of mass from\nstars is still a factor of ~ 100 slower than the accretion of gas from the\ndisc. Thus, it seems accretion of stars is not a major contributor to black\nhole mass growth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Apr 2016 20:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-27"}
