arsely samples the same volume. We demonstrate that these studies are\npossible in the Euclid Deep survey, i.e. in a redshift range in which\nenvironmental effects are different from those observed in the local universe,\nhence providing new constraints for galaxy evolution models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Apr 2016 20:00:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Jul 2016 09:39:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-31"}
