 reactions of ammonia, which means that all the nuclei are mixed in\nreactive collisions. If, instead, these reactions occur through proton\nhop/hydrogen abstraction processes, statistical spin ratios are to be expected.\nThe present results suggest that while the deuteration of ammonia changes with\nphysical conditions and time, the nuclear spin ratios of ammonia isotopologues\ndo not probe the evolutionary stage of a cloud.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Apr 2016 14:44:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Dec 2016 12:20:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-05"}
